{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3179783e-e716-447b-a491-0df3de353572","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) while keeping TRX + code coverage:\n\n## 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd these to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n## 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\n```yaml\n# Before:\n# - task: VSTest@3\n#     inputs:\n#       testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n#       resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n#       codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After:\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --logger \"trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n## 3. Publish results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\nFor Cobertura format coverage (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add this NuGet package to your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n```\n\nAnd change the collect argument to:\n\n```\n--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n**Key differences from VSTest@3:**\n- Tests are built & run via `dotnet test` instead of discovering pre-built DLLs\n- TRX + coverage publishing become explicit separate steps\n- `condition: succeededOrFailed()` ensures results publish even on test failure","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bb86f599-b8fa-4ddb-bc9a-cc5a23df3df2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. I'll provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":637,"requestId":"5C2F:236247:A117A:C9736:69F54AD5"},"id":"b9f5af50-35e8-40aa-b1b7-300cd855eecc","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:52:49.490Z","parentId":"c28f60d3-93ba-4aa5-8fdf-be184c7a50ae"}
